informal_statement:
If $E(X^2)$ is finite, then so is $E(|X|)$. We then have
[
\sigma^2(X) = E(X^2) - (E(X))^2;
]
consequently,
[
(E(|X|))^2 \le E(X^2).
]

informal_proof:
Suppose $X\sim\mathrm{Poisson}(\lambda)$, so for $k\ge 0$,
[
f(k)=e^{-\lambda}\frac{\lambda^k}{k!}.
]
For $k\ge 1$,
\begin{align*}
\frac{f(k-1)f(k+1)}{f(k)^2}
&=
\frac{\left(e^{-\lambda}\frac{\lambda^{k-1}}{(k-1)!}\right)
\left(e^{-\lambda}\frac{\lambda^{k+1}}{(k+1)!}\right)}
{\left(e^{-\lambda}\frac{\lambda^{k}}{k!}\right)^2}
=
\frac{k!^2}{(k-1)!(k+1)!}
=
\frac{k}{k+1}
\le 1,
\end{align*}
so $f(k-1)f(k+1)\le f(k)^2$.

informal_statement:
Let $z_{1}$ and $z_{2}$ be complex numbers. Show that
[
\sin z_{1}=\sin z_{2}
\Longleftrightarrow
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
z_{1}=z_{2}+2k\pi,\qquad \text{for some } k\in\mathbb{Z},\ \text{or}\\[4pt]
z_{1}+z_{2}=(2k+1)\pi,\ \text{for some } k\in\mathbb{Z}.
\end{array}
\right.
\]

informal_proof:
We have
[
\sin z_{1}-\sin z_{2}
=2\cos\!\left(\frac{z_{1}+z_{2}}{2}\right)\sin\!\left(\frac{z_{1}-z_{2}}{2}\right)
]
and hence
[
\sin z_{1}=\sin z_{2}
\Longleftrightarrow
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
\frac{z_{1}+z_{2}}{2}\in \frac{\pi}{2}+\pi\mathbb{Z},\ \text{or}\\[4pt]
\frac{z_{1}-z_{2}}{2}\in \pi\mathbb{Z}.
\end{array}
\right.
\]

informal_statement:
Let $X\subset\mathbb{R}^n$ be compact and let
$f:X\to\mathbb{R}$ be continuous. Given $\varepsilon>0$, show there is an $M$ such that
for all $x,y\in X$,
[
|f(x)-f(y)|\le M|x-y|+\varepsilon.
]

informal_proof:
This is a direct result of the following corollary:
\begin{corollary}[Corollary 3.22]
Let $C$ be a closed affine subspace of $\mathcal{H}$. Then the following hold:

\begin{enumerate}
\item[(i)] Let $x$ and $p$ be in $\mathcal{H}$. Then $p = P_C x$ if and only if
\[
p \in C
\quad\text{and}\quad
(\forall y \in C)(\forall z \in C)\,\langle y - z \mid x - p\rangle = 0.
\tag{3.15}
\]
\end{enumerate}
\end{corollary}
